quotes.text: "Why not here, as well as in a feather bed, twenty years hence,"
quotes.speaker: Unknown

quotes.text: "You've hurt me!"
quotes.speaker: his

quotes.text: "Have I though,"
quotes.speaker: his

quotes.text: "I didn't go for to do it."
quotes.speaker: his

quotes.text: "How is it now?"
quotes.speaker: her

quotes.text: "Kiss it and make it well,"
quotes.speaker: her

quotes.text: "That's what mother used to do. Where's mother?"
quotes.speaker: him

quotes.text: "Mother's gone. I guess you'll see her before long."
quotes.speaker: him

quotes.text: "Gone, eh!"
quotes.speaker: her

quotes.text: "Funny, she didn't say good-bye; she 'most always did if she was just goin' over to Auntie's for tea, and now she's been away three days. Say, it's awful dry, ain't it? Ain't there no water, nor nothing to eat?"
quotes.speaker: her

quotes.text: "No, there ain't nothing, dearie. You'll just need to be patient awhile, and then you'll be all right. Put your head up agin me like that, and then you'll feel bullier. It ain't easy to talk when your lips is like leather, but I guess I'd best let you know how the cards lie. What's that you've got?"
quotes.speaker: her

quotes.text: "Pretty things! fine things!"
quotes.speaker: her

quotes.text: "When we goes back to home I'll give them to brother Bob."
quotes.speaker: her

quotes.text: "You'll see prettier things than them soon,"
quotes.speaker: her

quotes.text: "You just wait a bit. I was going to tell you though--you remember when we left the river?"
quotes.speaker: her

quotes.text: "Oh, yes."
quotes.speaker: her

quotes.text: "Well, we reckoned we'd strike another river soon, d'ye see. But there was somethin' wrong; compasses, or map, or somethin', and it didn't turn up. Water ran out. Just except a little drop for the likes of you and--and--"
quotes.speaker: her

quotes.text: "And you couldn't wash yourself,"
quotes.speaker: her

quotes.text: "No, nor drink. And Mr. Bender, he was the fust to go, and then Indian Pete, and then Mrs. McGregor, and then Johnny Hones, and then, dearie, your mother."
quotes.speaker: her

quotes.text: "Then mother's a deader too,"
quotes.speaker: her

quotes.text: "Yes, they all went except you and me. Then I thought there was some chance of water in this direction, so I heaved you over my shoulder and we tramped it together. It don't seem as though we've improved matters. There's an almighty small chance for us now!"
quotes.speaker: her

quotes.text: "Do you mean that we are going to die too?"
quotes.speaker: her

quotes.text: "I guess that's about the size of it."
quotes.speaker: her

quotes.text: "Why didn't you say so before?"
quotes.speaker: her

quotes.text: "You gave me such a fright. Why, of course, now as long as we die we'll be with mother again."
quotes.speaker: her

quotes.text: "Yes, you will, dearie."
quotes.speaker: her

quotes.text: "And you too. I'll tell her how awful good you've been. I'll bet she meets us at the door of Heaven with a big pitcher of water, and a lot of buckwheat cakes, hot, and toasted on both sides, like Bob and me was fond of. How long will it be first?"
quotes.speaker: her

quotes.text: "I don't know--not very long."
quotes.speaker: her

quotes.text: "Cocks and hens,"
quotes.speaker: her

quotes.text: "Say, did God make this country?"
quotes.speaker: her

quotes.text: "Of course He did,"
quotes.speaker: her

quotes.text: "He made the country down in Illinois, and He made the Missouri,"
quotes.speaker: her

quotes.text: "I guess somebody else made the country in these parts. It's not nearly so well done. They forgot the water and the trees."
quotes.speaker: Unknown

quotes.text: "What would ye think of offering up prayer?"
quotes.speaker: Unknown

quotes.text: "It ain't night yet,"
quotes.speaker: Unknown

quotes.text: "It don't matter. It ain't quite regular, but He won't mind that, you bet. You say over them ones that you used to say every night in the waggon when we was on the Plains."
quotes.speaker: Unknown

quotes.text: "Why don't you say some yourself?"
quotes.speaker: Unknown

quotes.text: "I disremember them,"
quotes.speaker: Unknown

quotes.text: "I hain't said none since I was half the height o' that gun. I guess it's never too late. You say them out, and I'll stand by and come in on the choruses."
quotes.speaker: Unknown

quotes.text: "Then you'll need to kneel down, and me too,"
quotes.speaker: Unknown

quotes.text: "You've got to put your hands up like this. It makes you feel kind o' good."
quotes.speaker: his

quotes.text: "The wells are to the right, my brothers,"
quotes.speaker: his

quotes.text: "To the right of the Sierra Blanco--so we shall reach the Rio Grande,"
quotes.speaker: his

quotes.text: "Fear not for water,"
quotes.speaker: his

quotes.text: "He who could draw it from the rocks will not now abandon His own chosen people."
quotes.speaker: his

quotes.text: "Amen! Amen!"
quotes.speaker: his

quotes.text: "Redskins"
quotes.speaker: his

quotes.text: "There can't be any number of Injuns here,"
quotes.speaker: his

quotes.text: "We have passed the Pawnees, and there are no other tribes until we cross the great mountains."
quotes.speaker: his

quotes.text: "Shall I go forward and see, Brother Stangerson,"
quotes.speaker: his

quotes.text: "And I,"
quotes.speaker: his

quotes.text: "and I,"
quotes.speaker: his

quotes.text: "Leave your horses below and we will await you here,"
quotes.speaker: His

quotes.text: "This is what they call delirium, I guess,"
quotes.speaker: His

quotes.text: "My name is John Ferrier,"
quotes.speaker: His

quotes.text: "me and that little un are all that's left o' twenty-one people. The rest is all dead o' thirst and hunger away down in the south."
quotes.speaker: His

quotes.text: "Is she your child?"
quotes.speaker: His

quotes.text: "I guess she is now,"
quotes.speaker: Unknown

quotes.text: "she's mine 'cause I saved her. No man will take her from me. She's Lucy Ferrier from this day on. Who are you, though?"
quotes.speaker: Unknown

quotes.text: "there seems to be a powerful lot of ye."
quotes.speaker: His

quotes.text: "Nigh upon ten thousand,"
quotes.speaker: His

quotes.text: "we are the persecuted children of God--the chosen of the Angel Merona."
quotes.speaker: His

quotes.text: "I never heard tell on him,"
quotes.speaker: his

quotes.text: "He appears to have chosen a fair crowd of ye."
quotes.speaker: his

quotes.text: "Do not jest at that which is sacred,"
quotes.speaker: John Ferrier

quotes.text: "We are of those who believe in those sacred writings, drawn in Egyptian letters on plates of beaten gold, which were handed unto the holy Joseph Smith at Palmyra. We have come from Nauvoo, in the State of Illinois, where we had founded our temple. We have come to seek a refuge from the violent man and from the godless, even though it be the heart of the desert."
quotes.speaker: John Ferrier

quotes.text: "I see,"
quotes.speaker: his

quotes.text: "you are the Mormons."
quotes.speaker: John Ferrier

quotes.text: "We are the Mormons,"
quotes.speaker: John Ferrier

quotes.text: "And where are you going?"
quotes.speaker: John Ferrier

quotes.text: "We do not know. The hand of God is leading us under the person of our Prophet. You must come before him. He shall say what is to be done with you."
quotes.speaker: John Ferrier

quotes.text: "If we take you with us,"
quotes.speaker: Unknown

quotes.text: "it can only be as believers in our own creed. We shall have no wolves in our fold. Better far that your bones should bleach in this wilderness than that you should prove to be that little speck of decay which in time corrupts the whole fruit. Will you come with us on these terms?"
quotes.speaker: his

quotes.text: "Guess I'll come with you on any terms,"
quotes.speaker: Ferrier

quotes.text: "Take him, Brother Stangerson,"
quotes.speaker: his

quotes.text: "give him food and drink, and the child likewise. Let it be your task also to teach him our holy creed. We have delayed long enough. Forward! On, on to Zion!"
quotes.speaker: his

quotes.text: "On, on to Zion!"
quotes.speaker: him

quotes.text: "You shall remain here,"
quotes.speaker: his

quotes.text: "In a few days you will have recovered from your fatigues. In the meantime, remember that now and forever you are of our religion. Brigham Young has said it, and he has spoken with the voice of Joseph Smith, which is the voice of God."
quotes.speaker: Unknown
